	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44737><span id= >Kione</span></a><br><span id=notbold>151 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.68]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The simple fact of the matter is look at the damn title of the belt: it is the "Silvery Belt of Contention."&nbsp;&nbsp;Its *designed* to be wanted by *everyone.*  It has a phenominal AC and good stats for a caster, and it has haste for a melee.  Not only that, but its not No Drop.  Everyone can use it (unless by some miracle they have something better in their waist slot,) everybody will want it, everybody should have a roll on it.  Its not even so Uber that you know the guild will have already decided on who should get it (like, say Yelinak's Talisman which is AC 8, +7 to everything, +40 mana and HP with a haste effect.)  But, considering the other beltwear out there, everyone will want it.<br><br>If you're going to rule out casters because of the haste effect, heck, why not rule out Paladins because their PoA belt blows this away (better stats and a better haste.)  Rule out Warriors, Rogues, and Monks because it has Int and Wis (what do they need with a +5 to both!)  That leaves SKs, Rangers and Bards.  Wait, don't Bards not melee after a certain level?  Rule them out too!  And I'm sure if you really want to, you can figure out a way to rule out Shadowknights and Rangers.  There!  Now use this formula (with one important exception) to justify why everyone but your class should be excluded from the roll!<br><br>Your justification of ruling out Rangers, Bards, and casters is just as arbitrary as what I've outlined above.  If you really want to tick off all of these people in your group/raid, be my guest.  But don't be surprised if they take extreme exception to your view, and maybe look elsewhere in the future for raiding partners.<br><br>Of course, this item is nicknamed "Guild-breaker" for a reason. ;)  Frankly, the only way I see to not piss off somebody is to let *everybody* roll on it.  You would be well advised to think on that.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
